            <p>Banjo-Kazooie director Greg Mayles has confirmed he's now left Rare after 36 years at the British studio.</p>
<p>News broke of his <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/sea-of-thieves-and-banjo-kazooie-director-gregg-mayles-reportedly-leaving-rare-after-35-years">departure in the wake of layoffs at Microsoft</a> back in July, but now Mayles himself has announced his departure on social media - fittingly, with a rhyme.</p>
<p>N64 platformer Banjo-Kazooie was known for its script of rhyming couplets, and this charming post references plenty of the games Mayles worked on, from Battletoads and Donkey Kong, to Grabbed by the Ghoulies and <a href="https://www.eurogamer.net/games/viva-piata">Viva Piñata</a>.</p>

